Description: In an effort to "thin the herd", up for auction is my 60th Anniversary 2014 American Standard Stratocaster in Jade Pearl Metallic.I have owned this guitar since new and has been an in-home only guitar. Always stored in a smoke-free home in it's originalhardshell case(included). The guitar is in great shape and was rarely played. What can I say, I went "hardtail" right after purchasingthis and never even installed the tremolo arm. The spring saver sticker is still covering the threads. The tremolo is not blocked, I switched to a hardtail Stratocaster and haven't looked back. Please review the photographs before bidding as they are a key part of the description. Some of the features;25.5 scale Maple NeckMaple Fret-boardFender Custom Shop pickups SSSFactory hardshell case As with any electric guitar, it will need to be setup to your preferred playing style as everyone has their own comfort zone. This auction is for the lower 48 states in the United States only. As a used guitar it is being sold "as is" with no returns. Again, please review the photographs as a key part of the description before bidding. Item will be shipped within 48 hours after payment baring Sundays and federal holidays. Any bidders with less then ten feedback or excessive negative feedback will need to contact me before bidding. Thank you.
